The seven-episode series, which premiered on BBC One last September and was renewed for a second season, was filmed mostly in Prague.
“It was one of the few European cities not decimated in the war,” Hunt says.
“I know that through the lens of Spectrum they seemed to be very happy with how we did [the revival].
We were very adamant that we didn’t want to commit to more than one season because we didn’t know how this would go.